aiResponses.question_33402666002:
I do not require specific accessibility accommodations at this time, but I appreciate an inclusive interview approach and a chance to request adjustments if needed. In the past at TechCorp I worked across distributed teams in the US and EMEA and found that offering recordings, written summaries, and flexible scheduling significantly improved collaboration and participation for teammates with varying needs.

If helpful, I prefer interview schedules that consider time zone differences (Central Time) and appreciate short written agendas or bullet-point topics ahead of time so I can prepare focused examples (for example, CI/CD security improvements I led at TechCorp). I also find captioned video calls and the option to switch to a chat-based Q&A useful for technical whiteboarding or detailed code walkthroughs.

If any accommodations would make the process easier (adjusted timing, extended Q&A time, or alternative formats for technical tasks), Iâ€™m happy to coordinate with your recruiting team. I value an accessible process and am glad to work with you to ensure interviews are productive for everyone.
